dsDescriptionValue.value: ELSOC has been designed to evaluate the way in which Chileans think, feel and behave regarding a set of social issues related to conflict and social cohesion in Chile. Because its nature, this study it seeks to analyze, in a national representative sample, the stability or change in several social dimensions attending factors that can moderate or explain it trhough years.

value: Men and women, Chilean or foreign, from 15 to 75 years old, regular residents of occupied private dwellings (6 months or more livintg there at the time of interview), located in 40 cities (92 communes) of 13 regions of Chile.

fields.value: Centro Micro Datos (CMD), Facultad de Economía y Negocios. Universidad de Chile

Hiring interviewers with experience in complex and/or longitudinal surveys. Centralized and face-to-face training for field coordinators and a subset of interviewers in Santiago (including practical exercises for the implementation of the questionnaire, use of tablet and contact protocol). Additional activities in other regions of Chile. Design of a specialized Interviewer's Manual for the project.

Probabilistic, stratified and multi-stage sample design. Size proportional to Primary Sampling Units (census blocks). The Secondary Sampling Units are occupied private dwellings and the Tertiary Sampling Units are individuals. Survey representative of 93% of urban population and 77% of national population. Response Rate (RR2): 62%. Refusal Rate (REF2): 8.9%
In-person (face-to-face) interviewing in respondent household. Computer-assisted personal interviews (CAPI).
Quantitative study with a structured questionnaire, composed of close-ended questions of simple or multiple choice and some open-ended questions (numeric values as answer).

Response Rate: 62.4%
Cooperation Rate: 86.0%
Rejection Rate: 8.9%
Contact Rate: 72.6%
Mean Duration: 55 minutes
Monetary incentives  to respondent ($6.000 CLP), delivery of material about the study (ELSOC and COES) and follow-up actions based on contact information (Email for birthdays and holidays).

Use of CAPI system (tablets) for interviewing. The application developed for the questionnaire performs a validation check on responses. The field coordinators supervises the work of interviewers checking the number of visits, the contact, the identity of participant and few key questions. CMD performs an internal supervision of at least 10% of sample (interviewing again to some respondents) and checking duration and pattern response. ELSOC Survey Team analyze the consistency between waves of responses.

Calculus of sampling weights according to:

1) Base probability of selection.
2) Non-response Adjustment
3) Adjustment based on number of cases (regional population)
4) Adjustment based on number of cases (regional population and age)

Details are found in the ELSOC User Manual.
